HEADWORD: Torose
<hw>To*rose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>torosus</ets> full of muscle, brawny, fleshy. See
<er>Torus</er>.]</ety> <def>Cylindrical with alternate swellings and
contractions; having the surface covered with rounded
prominences.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

